bathing, swimming, or enjoying beachside refreshments (~3 hrs).\n- **Afternoon**: Visit the **National Art Museum of Catalonia (MNAC)** [INDOOR] - Discover the rich collection of Catalan art, including medieval and modern pieces (~2 hrs).\n- **Evening**: Stroll along **Passeig de Gràcia** [OUTDOOR] - Enjoy the elegant boulevard known for its shopping and architectural gems before dining at a restaurant on the street (~2.5 hrs).\n\n#### Day 5 - [Final Explorations]\n- **Morning**: Explore **Casa Batlló** [INDOOR] - Experience another of Gaudí's masterpieces, known for its unique design and vibrant colors (~1.5 hrs).\n- **Afternoon**: Visit **El Raval** Neighborhood [OUTDOOR] - Walk through this diverse area filled with street art and cultural spots for some last-minute sight-seeing (~2 hrs).\n- **Evening**: End your trip with a farewell dinner at **Tickets** [INDOOR] - Savor innovative cuisine at this acclaimed culinary hotspot (reservations recommended) (~2.5 hrs).\n\nThis itinerary provides a balanced mix of outdoor and indoor activities while focusing on art and food, fitting the conditions you provided. Enjoy your trip to Barcelona!"}
